  "decision_conditions": [
    "&lt;div&gt;The applicant has failed to submit sufficient information to demonstrate that the public benefit of the air source heat pumps, in terms of the improvement to the energy efficiency of the building, is sufficient to outweigh the visual harm to the character and appearance of the South Shoreditch Conservation Area that would result from the size and location of the proposed air source heat pump enclosures.&amp;nbsp; As such the proposal is contrary to policies D4 (Delivering good design), HC1 (Heritage conservation and growth) and SI2 (Minimising greenhouse gas emissions) of the London Plan 2021 and policies LP1 (Design Quality and Local Character), LP3 (Designated Heritage Assets), LP54 (Overheating and Adapting to Climate Change) and LP55 (Mitigating Climate Change) of the Hackney Local Plan 2020.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;"
